         Yer right about the melee/caster/hitting bit.  Melee's can hit anything.  Except if for some odd reason they are wearing normal armor and are trying to fight some magical beast, like a Pixie or whatever those funky blue floating things in Commons are.  My warrior, in his younder years, tried to pick a fight with one of those, and could only hit by kicking because his boots was the only Magical item he had.</P><P>Couple questions though:</P><P>If a spell lands on a beast, does it always do full damage?  If that was the case, than I can see why we'd be resisted.  A melee's damage fluctuates from a pansy weak hit to a nice crippling blow.  But my Spirit Tap always sucks 150 hp away.  </P><P>If that is the case, than to me it's a bit more understandable.  But if what I'm hearing is also true, that some beasts are near impossible to drop a load on, then something there should be changed.  Like most o' the beasts be immune (if at all) to only what their surroundings are like (naggy is immune to fire, but can get poisoned, so on so forth...).  </P><P>Or uhhh, something like that.<BR>'Course I could be just spouting nonsense.  If so, someone smack me.</P><P><font size=1>Racaus Camarillo<BR>Quellious<BR>Healers United (isn't that a hoot?)</font id=size1><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
